    <p>The peo­ple who chased and re­strained a man for al­legedly tak­ing up­skirt pic­tures in Lit­tle In­dia last year had not used ex­ces­sive force, and the man’s death was due to a “nat­u­ral disease process”, said State Coro­ner Ka­mala Pon­nam­palam. But she added that it is prefer­able and safer for the po­lice to han­dle such mat­ters.</p>


